# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#   YouTube Analyst — .env template
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy to `.env`, fill in real values, keep `.env` gitignored.

# ── YouTube Data API ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The channel ID to analyze. NOT the @handle — the canonical ID that
# starts with "UC…". Find yours at:
#   https://www.youtube.com/account_advanced
# or on any channel page: view source, search for "externalId".
YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID=

# How many days back each report covers.
REPORT_WINDOW_DAYS=7

# ── Google Sheets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# An existing Sheet where weekly metrics get appended. Create one in
# Drive first and paste its ID here (the string between /d/ and /edit
# in the URL). The runner will append a new tab per report.
GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=

# ── Google Slides ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL — a Slides presentation to use as a template. The runner
# copies this deck and fills in the placeholders. If blank, it creates
# a fresh deck from scratch.
# Template placeholders it looks for (plain text inside a text box):
#   {{CHANNEL_NAME}}  {{WINDOW}}  {{VIEWS}}  {{WATCH_HOURS}}
#   {{SUBS_GAINED}}   {{TOP_VIDEO_TITLE}}   {{TOP_VIDEO_VIEWS}}
GOOGLE_SLIDES_TEMPLATE_ID=

# ── Gmail ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The report is sent FROM the authenticated Gmail user (same account
# you sign into during the OAuth flow). These are the recipients:
REPORT_RECIPIENTS=you@example.com

# Subject line override (optional — defaults are fine).
REPORT_SUBJECT=
